description:
In `activitypub.rs:830-835`, when an account has no `recovery_pubkey` (pre-backfill accounts), the DID document is served with a zeroed `[0u8; 32]` recovery key:

```rust
None => {
    // Account has no recovery key yet; use a zeroed placeholder
    [0u8; 32]
}
```

This produces a syntactically valid DID document with a meaningless Ed25519 public key (the point for the all-zeros scalar). A consumer trusting this key would accept signatures from anyone who derives the well-known zeroed key. The endpoint should return 404 or omit the recovery key verification method entirely when no recovery key exists, rather than serving a predictable placeholder.

Affected: src/activitypub.rs:820-836
